deck:
George Seefurth Elrick (October 7, 1921 – December 29, 1997) was the author of several children's books and science fiction screenplays for television.

Elrick wrote 38 books, including Science Fiction Handbook for Readers and Writers, published by Chicago Review Press, and wrote for the Wild Kingdom.
